WEBVTT

00:00.770 --> 00:04.315
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren, and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons.

00:04.776 --> 00:09.523
This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:10.184 --> 00:18.356
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you.

00:18.476 --> 00:27.750
So get ready to be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the church.

00:29.112 --> 00:30.354
The glory of God.

00:30.466 --> 00:36.095
in the face of Jesus Christ, a sermon by Charles Spurgeon, part 1.

00:37.256 --> 00:49.335
For God, who commanded the light to shine out of darkness, hath shined in our hearts, to give the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

00:49.355 --> 00:53.842
2 Corinthians chapter 4 verse 6

00:55.330 --> 01:00.758
The apostle is explaining the reason for his preaching Christ with so much earnestness.

01:01.760 --> 01:06.727
He had received divine light, and he felt bound to spread it.

01:08.310 --> 01:12.636
One great motive power of a true ministry is trusteeship.

01:13.678 --> 01:16.542
The Lord has put us in trust with the gospel.

01:17.484 --> 01:21.490
He has filled us with a treasure with which we are to enrich the world.

01:22.562 --> 01:27.747
The text explains in full what it is with which the Lord has entrusted us.

01:28.828 --> 01:35.956
He has bestowed upon us the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

01:36.636 --> 01:50.130
And it is our duty to reflect the light, to impart the knowledge, to manifest the glory, to point to the Savior's face and to proclaim the name of Jesus Christ, our Lord.

01:51.490 --> 01:58.079
Having such a work before us, we must not faint, but press onward with our whole heart.

02:00.462 --> 02:09.353
With no other preface than this, I will direct your attention this morning first to the subject of that knowledge, in which Paul delighted so much.

02:10.314 --> 02:16.602
What was this knowledge, which to his mind was the chief of all, and the most worthy to be spread?

02:17.584 --> 02:19.346
It was the knowledge of God.

02:20.418 --> 02:31.414
for a man or woman, not to know their maker and ruler is deplorable ignorance indeed.

02:32.396 --> 02:34.940
The proper study of humanity is God.

02:36.021 --> 02:41.690
Paul not only knew that there is a God, for he had known that before his conversion.

02:42.711 --> 02:46.978
None can more surely believe in God than did Paul as a Jew.

02:47.038 --> 02:49.842
Nor does he merely intend to believe in God as a Jew.

02:49.986 --> 03:00.121
that he had learned of the character of God, for that also he had known from the Old Testament Scriptures before he was met with on the way to Damascus.

03:01.503 --> 03:11.638
But now he had come to know God in a closer, clearer and sure away, for he had seen him incarnate in the person of the Lord Jesus Christ.

03:13.181 --> 03:16.786
The Apostle had also received the knowledge of the glory of God,

03:17.922 --> 03:21.826
Never had the God of Abraham appeared so glorious as now.

03:23.187 --> 03:29.633
God in Christ Jesus had won the adoring wonder of the apostles' instructed mind.

03:30.934 --> 03:35.218
He had known Jehovah's glory as the one and only God.

03:36.099 --> 03:41.604
He had seen that glory in creation declared by the heavens and displayed upon the earth.

03:42.725 --> 03:47.730
He had beheld that glory in the law which blazed from Sinai.

03:48.066 --> 03:50.410
and shed its light upon the face of Moses.

03:51.571 --> 04:03.649
But now, beyond all else, he had come to perceive the glory of God in the face or person of Jesus Christ, and this had won his soul.

04:03.689 --> 04:12.663
This special knowledge had been communicated to him at his conversion, when Jesus spoke to him out of heaven.

04:12.703 --> 04:14.866
In this knowledge,

04:15.074 --> 04:29.415
He had made great advances by experience and by new revelations, but he had not yet learned it to the full, for he was still seeking to know it perfectly by the teaching of the divine spirit.

04:30.217 --> 04:41.874
And we find him saying that I may know him and the power of his resurrection and the fellowship of his sufferings being made conformable unto his death.

04:42.978 --> 04:48.025
Paul did not merely know God, but God in Christ Jesus.

04:49.247 --> 04:54.594
Not merely the glory of God, but the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

04:56.116 --> 05:00.522
The knowledge dealt with God, but it was Christ revealed knowledge.

05:01.664 --> 05:06.851
He pined not for a Christless Theism, but for God in Christ.

05:07.893 --> 05:11.858
This, beloved, is the one thing which you and I should aim to know.

05:12.706 --> 05:16.992
There are parts of the divine glory which will never be seen by us in this life.

05:18.074 --> 05:19.556
Speculate as we may.

05:21.058 --> 05:24.824
Mysticism would attempt to pry into the unknowable.

05:26.046 --> 05:33.837
You and I may leave dreamers and their dreams and follow the clear light which shines from the face of Jesus.

05:35.740 --> 05:39.826
What of God it is necessary and beneficial for us to know.

05:39.866 --> 05:42.450
He has revealed in Christ

05:43.234 --> 05:49.440
and whatever is not there, we may rest assured it is unfit and unnecessary for us to know.

05:49.460 --> 06:11.922
Truly, the revelation is by no means scant, for there is vastly more revealed in the person of Christ than we shall be likely to learn in this mortal life, and even eternity will not be too long for the discovery of all the glory of God which shines forth in the person of the word made flesh.

06:12.962 --> 06:21.273
those who would supplement Christianity had better first add to the brilliance of the Son, or the fullness of the sea.

06:22.515 --> 06:37.275
As for us, we are more than satisfied with the revelation of God in the person of our Lord Jesus, and we are persuaded of the truth of His words, He that hath seen me hath seen the Father.

06:39.157 --> 06:39.858
Hope not

06:40.066 --> 06:43.952
My brothers and sisters that the preacher can grapple with such a subject.

06:44.713 --> 06:46.195
I am overcome by it.

06:47.196 --> 06:51.342
In my meditations I have felt lost in its lengths and breaths.

06:52.765 --> 07:07.506
My joy is great in my theme, and yet I am conscious of a pressure upon brain and heart, for I am like a little child wandering among the mountains, or as a lone spirit which has lost its way among the stars.

07:08.386 --> 07:10.569
I stumble among sublimities.

07:11.270 --> 07:13.333
I sink amid glories.

07:14.775 --> 07:19.681
I can only point with my finger to that which I see, but cannot describe.

07:20.923 --> 07:26.411
May the Holy Spirit Himself take the things of Christ and show them unto you.

07:28.293 --> 07:34.802
We will, for a minute or two, consider this glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ historically.

07:36.290 --> 07:43.098
In every incident of the life of Jesus of Nazareth, the Lord's anointed, there is much of God to be seen.

07:44.740 --> 07:53.331
What volumes upon volumes might be written to show God has revealed in every act of Christ from his birth to his death.

07:54.773 --> 08:05.746
I see him as a bay but Bethlehem, lying in a manger, and there I perceive a choice glory in the mind of God, for he evidently despises the pomp

08:05.890 --> 08:11.318
and the glory of the world, which little minds esteem so highly.

08:12.579 --> 08:27.880
He might have been born in marble halls and wrapped in imperial purple, but he scorns such things, and in the manger among the oxen we see a glory which is independent of the trifles of luxury and parade.

08:29.603 --> 08:34.770
The glory of God in the person of Jesus asks no aid

08:35.010 --> 08:42.760
from the splendor of courts and palaces, yet even as a babe, he reigns and rules.

08:44.202 --> 08:57.979
Mark how the shepherds hastened to salute the newborn king, while the Magi from the far-off east bring gold, frankincense, and mer, and bow at his feet.

08:59.341 --> 09:03.186
When the Lord condescends to show himself in little things,

09:03.522 --> 09:08.129
He is still right royal and commands the homage of mankind.

09:09.230 --> 09:21.608
He is as majestic in the minute, as in the magnificent, as royal in the babe at Bethlehem, as in afterdays in the man who rode through Jerusalem with Hosanna's.

09:23.411 --> 09:31.122
See the holy child Jesus in the temple when he is but 12 years old, sitting in the midst of the doctors,

09:31.586 --> 09:33.849
astonishing them with his questions.

09:35.252 --> 09:37.755
What wisdom there was in that child.

09:39.278 --> 09:45.888
Do you not see here an exhibition of the truth that the foolishness of God is wiser than men?

09:45.948 --> 09:55.803
Even when God reserves his wisdom and gives forth utterances fit for a child, he baffles the wisdom of age and thought.

09:57.405 --> 10:00.370
Watch that youth in the carpenters' shop

10:01.154 --> 10:11.330
see Him planing and sawing, cutting and squaring, working according to His parents' command, till He is thirty years of age.

10:12.633 --> 10:13.694
What learn we hear?

10:14.616 --> 10:18.863
When we see the incarnate God tarrying at His workman's bench.

10:20.846 --> 10:23.150
Can we not see how God can wait?

10:24.312 --> 10:28.338
Is not this a masterly display of the leisure of the eternal?

10:29.666 --> 10:34.451
The infinite is never driven out of his restful pace of conscious strength.

10:35.612 --> 10:40.277
Had it been you and I, we should have hurried to begin our life work long before.

10:41.298 --> 10:45.803
We could not have refrained from preaching and teaching for so long a period.

10:46.784 --> 10:48.245
But God can wait.

10:49.366 --> 10:56.914
And in Christ, we see how prudence tempered zeal and made him share in that eternal leisure.

10:57.314 --> 11:01.318
which arises out of confidence that His end is sure.

11:03.140 --> 11:17.695
The fullness of God was concealed at Bethlehem and Nazareth from the eyes of sinful men and women, but it is revealed to those who have spiritual sight were with to behold the Lord.

11:19.797 --> 11:24.882
Even in those early days of our Lord, while yet He was preparing for His great mission,

11:25.410 --> 11:31.356
We behold the glory of God in his youthful face and we adore.

11:33.277 --> 11:37.561
As for his public ministry, how clearly the Godhead is there.

11:38.803 --> 11:44.728
Behold him, brothers and sisters, while he feeds 5,000 with a few loaves and fishes.

11:45.709 --> 11:51.374
And you cannot fail to perceive therein the glory of God in the provision of the universe.

11:52.876 --> 11:55.218
For the Lord God opens his hand

11:55.522 --> 11:58.385
and supplies the need of every living thing.

11:59.767 --> 12:04.513
See Him cast out devils and learn the divine power over evil.

12:05.834 --> 12:12.482
Hear Him raise the dead and reverence the divine prerogative to kill and to make alive.

12:14.084 --> 12:20.232
See Him cure the sick and think you hear Jehovah say, I wound, I heal.

12:21.253 --> 12:25.458
Hear how He speaks and infallibly reveals the truth

12:25.890 --> 12:31.618
and you will perceive the God of knowledge to whom the wise-hearted owe their instruction.

12:33.101 --> 12:45.379
Set over against each other these two sentences, behold God exalted by His power, who teacheth like Him, and never man spake like this man.

12:46.941 --> 12:53.010
It is ever the Lord's way to make His truth known to those of humble and truthful hearts.

12:53.506 --> 12:57.710
and so did Jesus teach the sincere and lowly among men.

12:58.991 --> 13:08.861
Observe how Jesus dwelt among humanity, wearing the common smock frock of the peasant, entering their cottages and sharing their poverty.

13:10.262 --> 13:13.025
Mark how he even washed his disciples' feet.

13:14.346 --> 13:22.994
Here we see the condescension of God, who must stoop to view the skies and bow to see what angels do.

13:23.810 --> 13:27.636
and yet does not disdain to visit the sons of men.

13:28.958 --> 13:34.767
In wondrous grace he thinks of us and has pity upon our lowest state.

13:36.149 --> 13:47.747
See too the Christ of God, my brothers and sisters, bearing every day with the taunts of the ungodly, enduring such contradiction of sinners against himself.

13:49.109 --> 13:52.594
And you have a fair picture of the infinite patience

13:52.834 --> 13:56.541
and the marvelous long suffering of God.

13:56.561 --> 14:01.490
And this is no small part of his glory.

14:01.510 --> 14:02.793
Thank you for listening, friends.

14:03.073 --> 14:07.862
This podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

14:08.443 --> 14:16.498
